<br>
The circumstances make a huge difference.  In your case, your friends and guildmates helped you out, and this is what epic questing is all about.   However, *buying* your epic pieces is what really irks me.   I was offered insane amounts of phat lewts for both my Earth Staff and Crown before completing my epic.   I do wonder if that particular mage would really get the same experience out of obtaining his Orb as I did.   For me, it was an accomplishment...  for him, well, I don't know.  It just seems to me that there is nothing &quot;epic&quot; about skipping the challenge/opportunity of reaching the 7th Island in the Plane of Sky and buying a crown with the items you farmed from Sebilis instead.   *shrug*<br>
