_________________________________<br>
<br>
But even with buying epic quest items, it depends on the circumstances.  <br>
<br>
Let's say that Magexyz isn't in a guild(my scenario), or in a large enough guild to raid PoA and hand him a crown.  Now let's also say that he has real life commitments that keep him from ever attending a 2-3 day raid with some other guild(heavy work schedule, single parent, whatever).  <br>
<br>
Does that mean that Magexyz is any less deserving of his epic than you are, just because he chose a class where Verant decided to stick an epic piece at the end of a raid that spans two days(or more, depending on the guild)?   There are entire epic quests that can be done in the time it takes to get to(and clear) island 7.  <br>
<br>
It's definately a different story if the person is just too lazy to try and earn it on their own, but if they can't for non-EQ reasons, I don't blame them at all for attempting to buy or trade for it.<br>
