<br>
I don't think even &quot;buying&quot; the items for the quest should be frowned upon, much less a concerted effort by friends.<br>
<br>
Multiquesting, I believe, was implimented to allow those shortcuts, doing away with the un-fun menial task of collecting mundane items that somebody already has.  There really is no reason for Joe to spend XX hours killing YY mobs to aquire XXno-dropXX item if Jane already has it and willing to help out Joe.  The game is designed to promote grouping, and multiquesting fits the foot.<br>
<br>
There are many quests which can be performed by races/classes, but those race/classes are prevented from aquiring specific items to complete the quest due to race/class hatred by NPC's.  Only by extreme length of time and effort by the quester - or by the time-saving generosity of another player - can the quester receive the reward.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
If you own a membership to a private club, but have a friend which is not - you can sponsor your friend which will get him/her in the club and eventually eligable for membership.  Much the same for the Ogre who faught in Karnors to get cobalt, lowering his faction to dubious in the Outpost - yet you can turn in 3 berz braids for every one of his to help him get his faction back in 25% of the time normally required.<br>
<br>
I have multiquested a quite a bit - for friendship, for guild, for charity, and for money - both giving and receiving.  It's not a cheat, it's not a exploit however you look at it or however it's done for whatever reason.  It's the way the game was meant to be played.<br>
<br>
Plus, if you think about it, looting a no drop quest item during a guild event is no less of a multiquest than having a friend turn in the item for you.  And, there's not always the class around to loot that no drop item - why let it rot? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/01 8:59:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Question on &quot;respectability&quot; of MultiQuestin</span><hr size=1> Congratulations on finishing your epic quest. <br>
