<br>
First, it's a personal thing - it's how you feel about it.<br>
<br>
To me, it lessens it. I'll share a couple decisions I made.<br>
But first, saying it lessons it doesn't mean it's not legitimate, not still a great accomplishment.<br>
<br>
I did my own air raids, asking for volunteers from many guilds. I believe I had a raid that could have got to island 7 finally, but some lag problems that were really terrible caused the last fight on isle 6 to be impossible. I ended up going with another guild and got the crown - they even summoned me to isle 7, I wasn't there for their 1-6 raid. This lessened it a bit for me, but I didn't care to ask friends to sacrifice another 2 days and money to help just for that.<br>
<br>
I multiquested the quillmane cloak (the only piece); but first, I spent dozens of play sessions over months in south karana trying to get my own. Did it lessen it for me? Yes, but I decided that there just wasn't much point in holding off on the epic over that item.<br>
<br>
The point I'm getting to, is that just because it's lessened a bit doesn't mean it's wrong. if you can't do a 3 day raid for an item, then you get the &quot;epic where you didn't do that 3 day raid&quot;. It still works great, it's still a great accomplishment for the rest of the effort you did, and it's probably the right thing to do.<br>
<br>
So enjoy it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One other aspect: I remember going with one of our powerful guilds as they just tore up plane of air. I just didn't feel like it'd mean as much getting it that way, if it was just show up and loot it. Interestingly, one of our uberguilds' mages is now advertising to buy the earth staff for multiquesting. Each person chooses their own way to play, and you can enjoy the game however you want.<br>
<br>
Any way you do it is legitimate, as long as you don't use an exploit/cheat. <p>Level 59 Conjurer, Master of the epic elemental magics, collector of robes<BR>
